{"id":14880726,"mediaExerciseId":"6e345553-f9b0-4aa1-9e18-7a3361e86f3e","exerciseName":"12","chapterName":"1","chapterTitle":"Introduction To Corporate Finance","groupId":612257,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":18,"solutions":[{"id":5890224,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine conflicts in maximizing the value of the stock.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/d3065079ba78c21fa24d1610c7d37bd6/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/d3065079ba78c21fa24d1610c7d37bd6/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The goal of the financial manager is to maximize the current market value of its equity, therefore maximizing shareholders' wealth.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/316f322e66e666df956a1b1519f2d98a/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":33,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/316f322e66e666df956a1b1519f2d98a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Our goal of maximizing the value of the stock can conflict with other goals as it may put pressure on management to perform. Managers may make poor decisions that can decrease the value of stock. They may also not always act in the interest of shareholders wealth, and act in their best interests instead.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/c8e9aebe237984a9100c23166602ea22/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":71,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/c8e9aebe237984a9100c23166602ea22/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Subjects like customer and employee safety, the environment, and the general good of society are essentially ignored because the current value of stock depends on management's value creation performance and on macro-economic factors.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/d87b18b8ac4e18115617be2d8e5a3df1/lateximg_large.png","width":1011},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/f71a0c91af7d7f6629db9478f52c8107/d87b18b8ac4e18115617be2d8e5a3df1/lateximg.png","width":507}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"14b17893-7217-4acb-b491-a85c64f7d268","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880727,"exerciseName":"13","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"09d28